import pytest
from implementation import Stack

class TestStack:
    def test_initially_empty(self):
        stack = Stack()
        assert stack.is_empty()

    def test_push_single_element(self):
        stack = Stack()
        stack.push(1)
        assert not stack.is_empty()
        assert stack.peek() == 1

    def test_push_multiple_elements(self):
        stack = Stack()
        stack.push(1)
        stack.push(2)
        stack.push(3)
        assert not stack.is_empty()
        assert stack.peek() == 3

    def test_pop_single_element(self):
        stack = Stack()
        stack.push(1)
        popped = stack.pop()
        assert stack.is_empty()
        assert popped == 1

    def test_pop_multiple_elements(self):
        stack = Stack()
        stack.push(1)
        stack.push(2)
        stack.push(3)
        popped = stack.pop()
        assert not stack.is_empty()
        assert popped == 3
        assert stack.peek() == 2

    def test_peek_empty_stack_raises_index_error(self):
        stack = Stack()
        with pytest.raises(IndexError):
            stack.peek()

    def test_pop_empty_stack_raises_index_error(self):
        stack = Stack()
        with pytest.raises(IndexError):
            stack.pop()

    def test_peek_does_not_remove_element(self):
        stack = Stack()
        stack.push(1)
        assert stack.peek() == 1
        assert stack.peek() == 1

    def test_is_empty_after_multiple_pushes_and_pops(self):
        stack = Stack()
        stack.push(1)
        stack.push(2)
        stack.pop()
        stack.pop()
        assert stack.is_empty()

    def test_peek_returns_last_pushed_element(self):
        stack = Stack()
        stack.push(1)
        stack.push(2)
        stack.push(3)
        assert stack.peek() == 3
